by that bitter Americano.

169
00:07:17,071 --> 00:07:18,031
That makes sense to me.

170
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:20,031
Besides, you look

171
00:07:20,591 --> 00:07:21,990
quite refreshed after drinking tea.

172
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:23,310
So I want to try it too.

173
00:07:24,071 --> 00:07:25,271
I'll bring you some later.

174
00:07:27,711 --> 00:07:28,951
By the way, Lucy mentioned

175
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:31,271
you had two client meetings
scheduled today,

176
00:07:31,591 --> 00:07:33,271
but both were
suddenly canceled by phone.

177
00:07:34,550 --> 00:07:36,591
You don't seem bothered by it.

178
00:07:37,191 --> 00:07:37,768
That's normal.

179
00:07:37,910 --> 00:07:39,271
This isn't the first time.

180
00:07:41,271 --> 00:07:42,271
Why not take this chance

181
00:07:42,310 --> 00:07:43,031
to take a break?

182
00:07:43,910 --> 00:07:44,751
Leave the work to me.

183
00:07:46,151 --> 00:07:47,071
It's been too long

184
00:07:47,071 --> 00:07:48,230
since you took your girl out.

185
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:49,591
Use this opportunity

186
00:07:50,151 --> 00:07:50,670
to unwind.

187
00:07:51,870 --> 00:07:54,191
Why are you worrying like those kids?

188
00:07:54,751 --> 00:07:55,751
Are you really okay?

189
00:07:56,191 --> 00:07:56,872
Yes.

190
00:08:00,430 --> 00:08:01,631
If those people saw you now,

191
00:08:01,670 --> 00:08:02,391
they'd be furious.

192
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:05,870
Your attitude is admirable.

193
00:08:05,951 --> 00:08:07,191
No anger phase.

194
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:08,470
Just calm.

195
00:08:09,831 --> 00:08:10,670
To be honest,

196
00:08:12,110 --> 00:08:13,110
I am pretty angry.

197
00:08:14,990 --> 00:08:16,670
Their slander this time

198
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:18,031
lacks any creativity.

199
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:21,151
A few years ago, the rumors

200
00:08:22,230 --> 00:08:22,951
were like,

201
00:08:23,631 --> 00:08:26,031
I had an affair
with a corporate executive,

202
00:08:27,071 --> 00:08:29,151
and left my ex-husband with nothing.

203
00:08:29,271 --> 00:08:30,751
And I yelled at clients.

204
00:08:31,470 --> 00:08:32,351
The craziest one.

205
00:08:34,070 --> 00:08:35,830
I was keeping a colleague from the firm.

206
00:08:36,631 --> 00:08:38,310
So dramatic and scandalous.

207
00:08:38,830 --> 00:08:40,550
This time, it's just boring nonsense.

208
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:44,710
"Keeping a colleague." I like it.

209
00:08:45,111 --> 00:08:46,710
If you need that, I'm available.

210
00:08:48,950 --> 00:08:49,710
Thanks a lot.

211
00:08:52,751 --> 00:08:53,288
Alright.

212
00:08:55,391 --> 00:08:56,991
Enough jokes. Let's talk business.

213
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:59,310
We should've done that sooner.

214
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:00,271
Come.

215
00:09:01,070 --> 00:09:03,031
Walking in pretending to comfort me.

216
00:09:03,231 --> 00:09:05,031
Procedures must be followed.

217
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,670
I reviewed Eddie's records
since joining.

218
00:09:07,944 --> 00:09:08,471
(Jiang Yutai)

219
00:09:08,471 --> 00:09:10,391
(Asia-Pacific Business Director)
He seems quite driven.

220
00:09:10,710 --> 00:09:12,511
He and Yan Da
are indeed childhood friends.

221
00:09:12,631 --> 00:09:14,550
They've gotten along well
these past few years.

222
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:16,991
But competition might change that.

223
00:09:17,471 --> 00:09:19,710
Xingke is a leader
in China's chip industry.

224
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:20,790
Recently,

225
00:09:20,871 --> 00:09:22,310
they've actively expanded overseas.

226
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:24,310
They're the biggest global rival

227
00:09:24,751 --> 00:09:26,430
to the foreign company Eddie worked for.

228
00:09:26,830 --> 00:09:27,590
Recently,

229
00:09:28,231 --> 00:09:30,070
they've taken APAC share
from Eddie's company.

230
00:09:30,871 --> 00:09:32,430
So the company's competitive motivation

231
00:09:32,871 --> 00:09:33,550
makes sense.

232
00:09:34,070 --> 00:09:35,471
But it seems incomplete.

233
00:09:36,231 --> 00:09:36,776
Incomplete?

234
00:09:39,310 --> 00:09:40,710
And I've also uncovered something.

235
00:09:41,231 --> 00:09:42,670
The Legal Director of this company

236
00:09:42,670 --> 00:09:43,830
is my old friend.

237
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:50,152
Ms. Bai.

238
00:09:50,751 --> 00:09:51,910
Given your current situation,

239
00:09:52,151 --> 00:09:54,631
you should keep these old friends away.

240
00:09:54,710 --> 00:09:56,151
Maintain some distance from them.

241
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:57,991
I think you're right.

242
00:09:58,590 --> 00:09:59,751
We're old friends, too.

243
00:10:00,871 --> 00:10:02,031
How could I be the same?

244
00:10:03,070 --> 00:10:04,190
These flowers

245
00:10:05,391 --> 00:10:06,351
are sugarcoated bullets.

246
00:10:06,471 --> 00:10:06,991
Unreliable.

247
00:10:09,471 --> 00:10:10,056
Fine.

248
00:10:10,430 --> 00:10:11,790
Out of everyone in this world,

249
00:10:11,790 --> 00:10:13,710
you're the most reliable one, Mr. Song.

250
00:10:14,151 --> 00:10:15,511
I never give sugarcoated bullets.

251
00:10:15,511 --> 00:10:16,631
What I offer is genuine.

252
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:18,991
If I ever find out
who's spreading dirt about you,

253
00:10:19,231 --> 00:10:20,391
I'll make sure they learn

254
00:10:20,391 --> 00:10:21,430
what real consequences

255
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:22,871
feel like.

256
00:10:23,310 --> 00:10:24,830
That's some dangerous talk.

257
00:10:25,590 --> 00:10:26,670
You're in non-litigation.

258
00:10:27,231 --> 00:10:29,871
Stop dancing on the edge
of criminal offenses

259
00:10:29,950 --> 00:10:31,070
with reckless testing.

260
00:10:31,151 --> 00:10:31,670
Got it?

261
00:10:31,670 --> 00:10:32,190
Enough.

262
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:34,351
Stop teasing me, will you?

263
00:10:36,271 --> 00:10:36,790
To business.

264
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:38,511
I have a tennis buddy,

265
00:10:38,631 --> 00:10:39,391
an industry contact

266
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:41,910
of Eddie and Yan Da.

267
00:10:43,190 --> 00:10:44,070
